    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot is slightly softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> to the dish with your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fish sauce </strong>with your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven and cook, uncovered, for an initial 22 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>mustard & coconut curry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong>, making sure all the rice is fully submerged</p><p>Cover very tightly with <strong>tin</strong> <strong>foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked rice</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the curry sauce has thickened, remove the dish from the oven and stir through the <strong>spinach</strong>, then add your <strong>white fish bites </strong>(unevenly sized white fish bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Gently stir it all together and return the dish to the oven for 7-8 min or until the white fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>baked Bengali-Style mustard & coconut white fish curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-bengali-style-mustard-and-coconut-white-fish-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>baked Bengali-Style mustard & coconut white fish curry</strong> with the <strong>baked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
